hopobject.body: Gloomy tales first choice medical supply mobile al With Apple's release of the new iPhone 5C and iPhone 5S last week, tech-hungry consumers will likely renew their cellphone contracts for another two years so they can get their hands on a shiny new iPhone at a price subsidized by their carrier ($99 to $199 compared to $650 or more without a contract). For those who aren't yet eligible for a two-year phone upgrade, carriers are also introducing plans like T-Mobile's JUMP! program that allow consumers to upgrade more than every other year.
